 5.3 - SASL Bind SASL is defined by RFC 4422 which obsoletes RFC2222. There are also a few RFCs that are related to SASL, they are listed in the next paragraph.
In any case, as ApacheDS and the Apache LDAP API are based on Java, we depend on the Java SASL impementation. Typically, this is handled by the SunSASL provider, which only support the following mechanisms, as of Java 8 :

Downloads LDAP API 1.0 Jar Download The Apache Directory LDAP API is distributed as a jar.
 Download Archive zip/tar.gz Download Sources  Maven Dependency The Apache Directory LDAP API is also available as a Maven dependency:
&lt;dependency&gt; &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.directory.api&lt;/groupId&gt; &lt;artifactId&gt;api-all&lt;/artifactId&gt; &lt;version&gt;${api-version}&lt;/version&gt; &lt;/dependency&gt;

Downloads LDAP API 2.1 Jar Download The Apache Directory LDAP API is distributed as a jar.
 Download Archive zip/tar.gz Download Sources  Maven Dependency The Apache Directory LDAP API is also available as a Maven dependency:
&lt;dependency&gt; &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.directory.api&lt;/groupId&gt; &lt;artifactId&gt;api-all&lt;/artifactId&gt; &lt;version&gt;${api-version}&lt;/version&gt; &lt;/dependency&gt;

